South Korean manufacturersâ€™
confidence held close to an 18-month low, signaling moderating
economic growth and a rise in the won have restrained sentiment.  An index measuring expectations for August rose to 91 from
90 for July, the Bank of Korea said in a statement in  Seoul 
today. The reading for July was the lowest since January 2010. A
measure of expectations at non-manufacturing companies fell to
83 from 84.  The survey, conducted from July 13 to July 20, was based on
responses from 1,611 manufacturers and 894 non-manufacturers.  To contact the reporters on this story:
